data.text:
"Three hundred years of Pennsylvania history, plus... Korean Billboard history, plus TikTok, plus Colorado history. This is a very historical episode of Time... C... R... I... S... I... Ssss..."

Episode[]

Guests[]

Daniel Ralston - music journalist

Topics[]

The Crew talk in depth about Van Halen and Eddie Van Halen's distinctive playing style, including his work on Michael Jackson's "Beat It". They touch on other heavy metal bands before talking about Jolly Rancher candies. Daniel Ralston joins to discuss the state of Pennsylvania and Hershey's products, including the Yuengling Hershey's Chocolate Porter. The Vampire Weekend "Campus" TikTok trend is explained with Ezra breaking down the song's meaning and the tendency of people to misinterpret the band's self-titled album. The episode closes out with a 2008 Top Five and musing on what the Vampire Weekend McDonald's meal would be like.
